        <div class="description"> Introduction to Substance Use Disorders
            This training provides a broad overview of how substance use progresses from experimental
             or recreational stages to severe dependence, offering counselors insight into key terms such
              as tolerance, withdrawal, and dependence. Participants will explore the biopsychosocial model 
              of addiction, which examines biological, psychological, and social factors contributing to 
              substance use. By completing this course, counselors can expect to gain a strong foundational 
              understanding of addiction, learn common terminology, and appreciate the complexity of factors
               that influence clients substance use.
            <a href="about_us.html"><br>Click Here To Access Training Page</a>

            <br><br>
            
        
