    <div class="description">Motivational Interviewing (MI) for Substance Use Disorders
        This training covers the principles of Motivational Interviewing—expressing empathy, 
        developing discrepancy, rolling with resistance, and supporting self-efficacy—and 
        demonstrates how to enhance client motivation and commitment to change. Through roleplays
         and skill-building activities, counselors learn to elicit clients own reasons for change
          and build stronger therapeutic alliances. Mastering MI empowers counselors to reduce resistance, 
          increase engagement, and support positive treatment outcomes.
        <a href="about_us.html"><br>Click Here To Access Training Page</a>

        <br><br>
        
    
