<div class="description">Family Systems Therapy for Addiction
    This training explores how family roles, dynamics, and communication patterns
     can perpetuate or mitigate substance use. Counselors learn to identify 
     behaviors like enabling and co-dependency and practice evidence-based 
     interventions that involve family members and partners in the recovery
      process. Upon completion, counselors will have strategies to strengthen 
      family support, resolve conflict, and improve overall relationship 
      functioning in the context of addiction treatment. <a href="about_us.html"><br>Click Here To Access Training Page</a>


    </div>
