<div class="description">Relapse Prevention & Continuing Care
This module emphasizes the identification of high-risk triggers
 and the development of effective coping strategies to support 
 long-term recovery. Counselors review aftercare planning, involving 
 mutual-help groups like 12-step or SMART Recovery, and learn how to 
 maintain client engagement post-treatment. Mastery of these skills 
 helps counselors foster clients resilience and reduce the likelihood 
 of relapse by creating robust support networks and sustainable routines.<a href="about_us.html"><br>Click Here To Access Training Page</a>


 
</div>

