<div class="description">Ethical Decision Making in High-Risk Situations
    Focusing on complex ethical dilemmas, this training addresses mandated
     reporting, confidentiality, and dual-role boundaries in substance use 
     disorder treatment. Participants practice applying ethical frameworks 
     to real-world scenarios, such as client relapse or domestic violence. 
     By the end, counselors will be more adept at navigating conflicting 
     obligations, protecting client welfare, and upholding professional standards.
    
    <a href="about_us.html"><br>Click Here To Access Training Page</a>

    </div>
 
    

