<div class="description">Criminal Justice Populations and Substance Use Disorders
    Counselors in this course examine specialized programs like drug courts,
     mental health courts, and re-entry initiatives, as well as the Risk-Need-
     Responsivity (RNR) model for offender rehabilitation. Training includes 
     implementing MAT and group interventions in correctional settings, 
     followed by strategies for reintegration into the community. Counselors
      will be prepared to serve justice-involved clients more effectively, 
      reducing recidivism and supporting lasting recovery.
    
    <a href="about_us.html"><br>Click Here To Access Training Page</a>

 

</div>

